WEBVTT

00:01.430 --> 00:07.360
What I want to show you is kind of like a step above what we did in the previous lesson.

00:07.370 --> 00:16.970
Let's start out by going into our gear and going into settings and going into labels now in labels.

00:17.020 --> 00:24.230
I'm going to create a new label called family I'm not nesting it under anything and click Create.

00:24.310 --> 00:30.450
Now I'm going to create another new label and I'm going to call it James as in my father in law.

00:30.500 --> 00:38.990
This one I am going to nest under the new one I just made quickly so I could have Bonnie I could have

00:38.990 --> 00:45.840
James I could have Joanne I could have family my sister down in Florida whatever family.

00:45.860 --> 00:46.690
Why.

00:46.730 --> 00:51.370
Because there's going to be so much going on with your mail.

00:51.530 --> 00:57.180
It's not a bad idea to make your own little categories and labels and start isolating things.

00:57.200 --> 01:00.140
So with that done let's go back in the inbox.

01:00.140 --> 01:05.660
When my father in law e-mails me it's not about business it's always about family could be about a recipe

01:05.660 --> 01:09.460
like it could be about I don't no new car but whatever.

01:09.920 --> 01:14.290
Isolate him so it doesn't clog up my e-mail with family business.

01:14.330 --> 01:16.350
So what I'm going to do is click here.

01:17.230 --> 01:23.700
And say if a mess derives from James I've already done this once with him on another project.

01:23.740 --> 01:25.500
So remember as I did that.

01:25.660 --> 01:26.980
Now that's all I need.

01:26.980 --> 01:32.450
I'm going to create a filter with this search when a message arrives that matches this search.

01:32.710 --> 01:38.270
Apply the label family James create a filter.

01:38.350 --> 01:38.980
That's it.

01:38.980 --> 01:43.090
The next time I get a message from him I can come over here.

01:43.570 --> 01:48.640
I can click James and all of his messages will be right there for me.

01:48.640 --> 01:51.420
Say well what if I don't want that one anymore.

01:51.550 --> 01:52.920
What if that was a mistake.

01:53.140 --> 01:58.480
We'll go back into settings and go into filter's.

01:58.730 --> 01:59.720
And there it is.

01:59.960 --> 02:07.010
So I can edit it or I can delete it creating these rules and I have on my other system the one I use

02:07.010 --> 02:07.640
in business.

02:07.850 --> 02:09.320
I have hundreds of rules.

02:09.390 --> 02:10.490
I have spam rules.

02:10.490 --> 02:11.580
I've got family rules.

02:11.580 --> 02:12.740
I got all kinds of rules.

02:12.950 --> 02:14.840
I got more rules that I need.

02:14.840 --> 02:18.960
But they can really help you and you can make the filter right here if you want to.

02:19.130 --> 02:22.780
Making filters and creating rules organizes you.

02:22.850 --> 02:23.410
Full stop.
